{"id":"fe1a64d7-a956-4516-81b1-3c4df97aa711","title":"1547/07: To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"9a154e1d-0ba0-46f3-8cc4-7f9768198e64","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, [July. 1547].","standoffProperties":[{"id":"ac7c7e02-38ec-4e03-8e80-0a35c6d390d1","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":3,"value":"8532f2fa-b614-4eed-9eae-586327f6a15a","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"61aea8df-9d8e-48a4-9b2c-f571a62a2b92","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d920ebcc-fad8-4396-87b4-cdcc4ebd5f5e","type":"codex/time-reference","start":12,"end":21,"value":"24e4d359-7eb6-4086-9a87-0a8f6ab16507","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"5d2ff06d-1f3e-4e7f-9803-622000ffe6fa","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"dfda47a7-57d7-463b-801f-74c408641cc7","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"6be2544f-1eec-42fd-a00d-b4c37d225a6f","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"959dc6ba-f25b-4d23-b10b-ddfeef30e936","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"8ecdf3ed-3260-4eab-b823-b59b344f201b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":1,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"5e718c42-64a2-4af8-8960-0ec0480b224c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"b5a53568-73dc-4bad-8b95-62e67c7517b9","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"eda334a1-0949-4938-bbaf-bea9f7316ac6","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0From thy last letter touching the purchase of the house I learn that Giovanni Corsi is dead and that thou art uncertain what his heirs will do about it. Thou writest also to say thou thinkest the house of Zanobi Buondelmonte is for sale. This would suit me twice as well as the Corsi house: but whichever of the two it may be, I think we ought not to hesitate over a matter of a hundred\u00A0crowns, provided that due care is exercised in\u00A0securing an investment free from all drawbacks. And this I think ought to be done with as little delay as possible; for as thou must take a wife, or desirest to take a wife, it would be better in every way for thee to marry before I die than to wait until I am in my grave. In order to send thee the remainder of the sum which I think may be lacking for the\u00A0purchase of either of the houses I will begin, perhaps during the coming week, to send thee a few crowns:\u00A0and as in thy letter thou hast mentioned a case deserving of charity, of the money I shall send thee thou art to give the woman whatever thou thinkest reasonable. I have no more to say. Salute Guicciardino and Francesca in my name. Commend me also to Messer Giovan Francesco, and ask him to forgive me for not having done as I ought. I have too much else to think of.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"f8561d0a-6dc7-4221-8206-5bf8f2e8f1ea","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"0bf187b9-c04e-4e0e-b010-8b3d6df2dfa0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d689636f-991b-4acf-bdeb-db5ddbf1ccf2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":17,"end":19,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"a95cb831-b441-4416-9c58-bd1ccab3f2e4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":62,"end":66,"value":"a7ca02e2-998f-444f-8b07-64f8240620a3","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id